      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:41:4",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ (عليه السلام) وُكِّلَ الرِّزْقُ بِالْحُمْقِ وَ وُكِّلَ الْحِرْمَانُ بِالْعَقْلِ وَ وُكِّلَ الْبَلَاءُ بِالصَّبْرِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473404\">H 14725</a> – A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Ubeyd Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al-Husayn, from Ali Bin Al-Husayn, from his father, from his grandfather who said:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>mir-ul-Momineen</span><sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The sustenance is allocated to the foolishness, and the deprivation to the intellect, and the affliction to the patience’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "277. A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Ubeyd Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al-Husayn, from Ali Bin Al-Husayn, from his father, from his grandfather who said: Amir-ul-Momineen (a.s.) said: ‘The sustenance is allocated to the foolishness, and the deprivation to the intellect, and the affliction to the patience’."
        ]
      }
    }
